==English==

{{rank|entirely|system|sister|727|occasion|enemy|perfect|bright}}

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʒən|-eɪʒən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[falling out]], [[happening]], or coming to pass; hence, that which falls out or happens; [[occurrence]]; incident.
# A [[favorable]] [[opportunity]]; a [[convenient]] or [[timely]] [[chance]]; [[convenience]].
# An occurrence or [[condition]] of [[affair]]s which brings with it some unlooked-for [[event]]; that which [[incidentally]] brings to pass an event, without being its efficient cause or sufficient reason; [[accidental]] or [[incidental]] cause.
# Need; [[exigency]]; [[requirement]]; [[necessity]]; as, I have no occasion for firearms.
# A [[reason]] or [[excuse]]; a [[motive]]; a [[persuasion]].

